article.headline: No. 5 Gonzaga knocks off Arizona 91-74 in Maui
article.linkText: No. 5 Gonzaga knocks off Arizona 91-74 in Maui
article.story: LAHAINA, Hawaii -- Rui Hachimura scored 24 points, Zach Norvell Jr. added 20 and No. 3 Gonzaga earned a spot in the Maui Invitational title game with a 91-74 win over Arizona Tuesday night. Gonzaga (5-0) was out of synch late in the first half after a good start, falling into an eight-point hole. The Zags turned the Lahaina Civic Center into The Kennel West early in the second, the cheers growing louder with each basket during a 15-2 run that put them up 56-53. Two-time Maui champion Arizona (4-1) fought back to keep it close, but only for a little while. Gonzaga went on another run, pushing the lead 79-67 and kept the Wildcats at bay from there. The Zags will face five-time Maui champion and top-ranked Duke in Wednesday's title game. Justin Coleman had 28 points for Arizona, which had three assists on 21 made field goals.

videos.headline: Jones puts Gonzaga in front with putback
videos.description: Zach Norvell Jr. can't finish on the inside, but Jeremy Jones is there to tip it off the glass and give the Bulldogs a 25-24 lead over the Wildcats.

videos.headline: Clarke punches home one-handed slam
videos.description: Zach Novell Jr. finds Brandon Clarke on the pick-and-roll for a vicious finish on the inside.

videos.headline: Rudolph goes coast-to-coast
videos.description: Brandon Randolph grabs the rebound and shows off his speed down the court, taking it all the way for a transition bucket.

videos.headline: Norvell reaches back for huge fast-break jam
videos.description: Zach Norvell Jr. knocks the ball free, then takes it all the way to the rim for a nasty one-handed dunk.

videos.headline: Norvell converts crafty scoop shot for and-1
videos.description: Zach Norvell Jr. attacks the rim and scoops it off the glass, finishing through contact for a 3-point play opportunity.

videos.headline: Rudolph gets friendly roll for big and-1
videos.description: Brandon Rudolph initiates contact with Rui Hachimura, hanging in the air and getting the roll to cut the Bulldogs' lead to 67-65.

videos.headline: Gonzaga turns defense into offense with fast-break bucket
videos.description: Zach Norvell Jr. gets a steal and hustles down the floor to clean up Rui Hachimura's miss, making it 71-65 Bulldogs.

videos.headline: Few on facing Duke in finals: 'We're looking forward to it'
videos.description: Gonzaga head coach Mark Few explains how his team turned it around against Arizona, and what they'll have to do to knock off No. 1 Duke in the championship.
